===============================================================================================
COMPILE :
linux@linux:~/Linux_programming/Memory_Management/xcalloc$ make
gcc -Wall -g -o xcalloc_op xcalloc.c;


===============================================================================================
Execution:
linux@linux:~/Linux_programming/Memory_Management/xcalloc$ ./xcalloc_op 

 Successfull xcalloc() 
linux@linux:~/Linux_programming/Memory_Management/xcalloc$ 


===============================================================================================
Program Flow
===============================================================================================
        use of  malloc() wrapper that prints an error message and terminates the program if
        malloc( ) returns NULL .
        By convention, developers call this common wrapper xmalloc( )





